20/05/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The association representing victims of the March 2008 Gerdec explosions sought financial compensation from the defence ministry on Wednesday (May 19th). 
"We will ask for about 140,000 euros for every victim. 
Our request is based on the law and we will wait 30 days for an answer," association head Feruzan Duda said. 
A total of 26 people died and 300 were injured when a weapons dismantling depot exploded in Gerdec. 
(Shekulli, Klan, Alsat, Top Channel - 19/05/10)
